  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I don't want to expose all JSON-RPC methods to DApps.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: In status-go, starting from commit `ef160e87`, we stripped down APIs exposed in `CallRPC`. So far, `CallRPC` could call **any** JSON-RPC method, even not whitelisted ones. \r\n\r\nIn `ef160e87`, we fixed that and `CallRPC` calls only public or whitelisted APIs. In order to call a private API (like `admin_*`), a new binding called `CallPrivateRPC` must be used.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n`CallRPC` can't call non-whitelisted APIs.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n`CallRPC` can call **any** JSON-RPC method.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- [ ] change `CallRPC` to `CallPrivateRPC` in internal usage (e.g. I remember we use `admin_peers` to check if MailServer is properly connected; after upgrading status-go to `ef160e87` it won't work with `CallRPC`),\r\n- [ ] upgrade status-go to `ef160e87`.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: any including 0.9.17\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n### Related changes\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/815\r\n- https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/825\r\n",
